OL,4,Cholidays: an anachronism
OL,6,FThat is, of course, if you still have
OL,7,Fa bank on your high street. In recent
OL,8,Fyears huge numbers of branches have
OL,9,Fclosed, causing very real worries for
OL,10,Fthose who prefer traditional banking
OL,11,Fand those with broader concerns about
OL,12,Ftown centres.
OL,14,FSome bank holidays are not observed in
OL,15,Fparticular towns or even nations. The
OL,16,FAugust bank holiday is not marked in
OL,17,FScotland where there is a holiday on
OL,18,FSt Andrew's Day (though few would
OL,19,Fnotice it).
