OL,3,CShorter news programmes on bank
OL,4,Cholidays: an anachronism
OL,6,FTake a typical BBC One bank holiday in
OL,7,Fthe late-eighties or nineties `
OL,8,Fchildren's programmes from 7am to late
OL,9,Fmorning, sport or a film in the
OL,10,Fafternoon, short news bulletins at
OL,11,Frandom times and an evening schedule
OL,12,Fwith little but, say, Wogan or
OL,13,FEastEnders to remind you it was a
OL,14,FMonday.
OL,16,FTomorrow could be called semi-normal.
OL,18,FThe big change on BBC One is that the
OL,19,FNews at One, regional news and News at
OL,20,FTen are shorter than usual. The Six is
OL,21,Freplaced by a shorter bulletin at
OL,22,F6.30pm.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/8
