OL,3,CShorter news programmes on bank
OL,4,Cholidays: an anachronism
OL,6,FEven this is still closer to normality
OL,7,Fthan a few years ago. There has been a
OL,8,Ftrend on BBC One towards running the
OL,9,Fnews closer to its normal times during
OL,10,Fholiday periods.
OL,12,FIn the event of a major story, it can
OL,13,Fbe safely assumed that the Ten might
OL,14,Fbe extended to its normal duration.
OL,16,FThe time has surely come for BBC One
OL,17,Fto go the whole hog and plan on the
OL,18,Fassumption it will run completely
OL,19,Fnormal news programmes on bank
OL,20,Fholidays ` it is already 80pc of the
OL,21,Fway there.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/8
