OL,3,CShorter news programmes on bank
OL,4,Cholidays: an anachronism
OL,6,FIn the English regions, there is a
OL,7,Fgreater reliance generally on features
OL,8,Fand human stories. Surely it would be
OL,9,Fbusiness as usual for them? The only
OL,10,Fquestion is about resourcing as they
OL,11,Fare often tight ships.
OL,13,FThe main news programmes are the
OL,14,Fcornerstone of BBC One and the bank
OL,15,Fholiday service is anachronistic.
OL,17,FThere's nothing wrong with having a
OL,18,Ffew bank holiday treats within the
OL,19,Fschedule ` Planet Earth III in the
OL,20,Fafternoon or The Boy, The Mole, The
OL,21,FFox and The Horse at teatime.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/8
